  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TCV72">
<l>pōtiṉmaṅkai pūtalakki ḻattitēvi yaṉṟiyum</l>
<l>pōtutaṅku nāṉmukaṉma kaṉavaṉma kaṉcolil</l>
<l>mātutaṅku kūṟaṉēṟa tūrtiyeṉṟu vētanū</l>
<l>lōtukiṉṟa tuṇmaiyalla tillaimaṟṟu raikkilē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>‘The woman on the lotus, the Earth lady are [His] wives; besides,</l>
<l>The four-faced [Brahmā] who dwells on a lotus is [His] son; to say [further],</l>
<l>His son is [Śiva] on whose [left] part a lady dwells, the bull-rider’</l>
<l>–what the Vedic treatises thus state is the truth. On the other hand,</l>
<l rend="indent">If one speaks contrary [to this], it is not [the truth].</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
